 The Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association of Nigeria has urged the South-East and South-South governors to involve its leadership in peace talks in the zones. The cattle breeders association also asked Christians to pray for peace and unity of Nigeria as they celebrate the resurrection of Jesus Christ. Alhaji Gidado Sidikki, South-East Zonal Chairman of MACBAN, made the call in a statement in Awka, Anambra State in his Easter message to Christians in the zones. The statement quoted Sidikki as saying that the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ was the pillar of the Christian faith and the celebration, adding that it was also a period to reflect on Messiah’s earthly mission characterised by good works It read that “Nigerian citizens should be encouraged to freely engage themselves anywhere across the country provided such engagement is legitimate. “The Federal Government should ensure that Nigerians doing businesses across their tribal lines are duly protected.” It also urged them to take advantage of the period to renew their faith in the unity and peaceful coexistence of Nigerians, saying, “With prayers and faith in God, the country will prosper and overcome all the challenges that threaten its unity. ‘As Christians celebrate the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ, I urge them to reflect on the lessons they learnt during the Lenten period. “Let us love one another and see ourselves as one indivisible entity in spite of our tribal differences.” 